problem.title: Math Issues
problem.markdown:
Oh no, our Math object was "accidentally" reset. Can you re-implement some of those functions? We can assure, that only non-negative numbers are passed as arguments. So you don't have to consider things like `undefined`, `null`, `NaN`, negative numbers, strings, etc.

Here is a list of functions, we need:

- Math.round()
- Math.ceil()
- Math.floor()
